{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_31","type":"agent_message","text":"{\"reviewer\":\"codex\",\"schemaVersion\":1,\"scores\":null,\"weightedTotal\":null,\"verdict\":\"FAIL\",\"issues\":[{\"severity\":\"P2\",\"location\":\"src/stores/space-store.ts:89\",\"description\":\"`loadMore` sets `isLoadingMore: true` and increments `_reqId`, but if a filter change or `fetchSpaces` invalidates that request before it resolves, the stale `loadMore` finally block skips clearing `isLoadingMore` because `_reqId` no longer matches. The stale data append is blocked, but the loading-more flag can remain true, so a subsequent filtered result with `hasMore: true` renders the \\\"더 보기\\\" button permanently disabled. The new race test verifies the stale append is ignored but does not assert `isLoadingMore` is reset.\",\"recommendation\":\"Clear pagination state when starting a full reload/filter change, or use separate request tokens/loading flags for `fetchSpaces` and `loadMore` so invalidated load-more requests still release `isLoadingMore`. Add a regression test where the replacement filter response has `hasMore: true` and assert `isLoadingMore === false`.\",\"defer\":false,\"deferRationale\":null,\"fixNow\":true},{\"severity\":\"P3\",\"location\":\"prisma/schema.prisma:153\",\"description\":\"The API now caps response size, but the global super-admin path still queries `where status = ACTIVE` ordered by `updatedAt desc, id desc` without a matching composite index. With many ACTIVE spaces, the database may still scan/sort a large candidate set for every page, so the original scale debt is only partially addressed at the query-plan level.\",\"recommendation\":\"Plan a migration for an index matching the hot order/filter, e.g. status plus `updatedAt`/`id` ordering, and validate with the target database's query plan. Consider owner/member scoped access patterns separately before choosing indexes.\",\"defer\":true,\"deferRationale\":\"This requires a database schema migration and query-plan validation beyond the read-only pagination patch; response-size correctness is still improved by the current change.\",\"fixNow\":false}]}"}}
